      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="zoor0354.transcription" corresp="#zoor0354.translation">
            <p>
               <g type="palm-branches"/>
               <lb/>
               <g type="sun-disc-with-inscribed-cross"/>
               <lb/>Εἷς Θεός,
               ὁ πάν<unclear>τ</unclear>
               <lb break="no"/>ων Δε<unclear>σπότ</unclear>ης <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
               <lb/>
               <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="zoor0354.translation" corresp="#zoor0354.transcription">
            <p> One (is) the God, the<lb/>Lord of all.....</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 4: The now lost fourth line contains several faded Aramaic letters, written
               upside-down in red paint. Probably remains of an earlier Jewish Aramaic inscription,
               placed in the opposite direction to that of the Greek one. </p>
         </div>
